      "writtenOn": "2026-05-26T11:49:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good point. This current range format won\u0027t be understood natively by mongo. In this representation it will understand the range only like s0:c123,c456. \nIt is possible to separate s0 and c123,c456 it two differents xattrs, but I don\u0027t see other ways to store the c123,c456 part (maybe a selinux.category entry containing a list of categories, could be too long)\n\nFor SELinux, c123,c456 represents c123 AND c456, but c123.c456 represents FROM c123 TO c456.",
      "parentUuid": "c1eeb0b2_6c4e94a9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 49,
        "startChar": 24,
        "endLine": 49,
